$ Shell command: usermod
@ usermod

`usermod` can be used to modify a → Linux/user[user's] account, for example to add a user to a → Linux/fhs/etc/group#add.

{ Adding a user to a group #add

  A user is added to a group with the → Linux/shell/commands/usermod command:
code {
sudo usermod -aG group-name user-name
code }

}


